<subSubSection pageNumber="529" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="529">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="529">Note:</emphasis>
This has been variously treated as either an orthographic variant of 
<taxonomicName authority="(L.) L. (1759)" authorityName="Pennell" authorityYear="1759" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1756" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Gratiola" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageNumber="529" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="monnieri">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="529">G. monnieri</emphasis>
(L.) L. (1759)
</taxonomicName>
, or an independent name. However, the former seems more appropriate, making the name homotypic with 
<taxonomicName authority="(L.) L." authorityName="Pennell" authorityYear="1759" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1756" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Gratiola" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageNumber="529" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="monnieri">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="529">G. monnieri</emphasis>
(L.) L.
</taxonomicName>
and its basionym 
<taxonomicName authority="L. (1756)" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1756" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Primulaceae" genus="Lysimachia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageNumber="529" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="monnieri">
